Lionel Messi was born in Rosario, Argentina in 1987 and started playing football at age five. He moved to Spain to join FC Barcelona after being sick as a child and despite being only 169 centimeters tall, he has become the best football player in the world and the top scorer for Barcelona and Argentina's national team.
